summary: ok ive been watching a lot of the pokemon sun and moon show recently (its so cute and i love it much!!) and ash is really adhd...
question: ok ive been watching a lot of the pokemon sun and moon show recently (its so cute and i love it much!!) and ash is really adhd there!!!!! i havent watched the original show since i was a kid but esp in this one hes super impulsive and hes loud and has a BIG hyperfixation on pokemon but hes really bad at focusing on other things!! and the way he comes to conclusions/trains his pokemon etc can be unconventional but hes still good bekdbdoddnd i dont know if i explained that well sorry this was long
answer:
Honestly yes, so much yes. This boy has been ADHD since the beginning of the show. I’m only familiar with Indigo League and it has been a very long time since I watched it, but I’m going to add a few things that I remember for sure.

ADHD Ash Ketchum from Pokemon!

  • Oh yes he’s so loud, and his special interest in pokemon is so so very obvious!
  • He sees things that others just don’t see and makes decisions that might seem nonsensical to his companions.
  • He forgets basic things (I very clearly remember an episode very near the beginning when he has to use his pokedex to find out what a rattata is. A rattata. One of the most common pokemon in any region.)
  • He also forgets that he needs to, like, eat and sleep and provide for basic needs because he’s so focused on training and getting better.
  • He thought that his metapod could win a battle with another metapod by repeatedly using harden, and that the other metapod would just… faint out of frustration or something?? So clearly some of his processing speeds are… quite slow.
  • There’s also one time when he tells an Arbok to use wrap on a jolteon and the arbok gets hurt by jolteon’s spikes. Which should have been pretty obvious, but when he’s in the thick of things, Ash tends to skip straight to the end of a line of logic… and leaves out a few important steps, such as “hang on this is dangerous”.
  • He starts off Indigo League, first thing, right out of the gate, by running late. Honestly what a mood.
